                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.75/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-08-26T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Exclusive telephone rights in Spain have been given to American telephone
                    interests who were assisted by Embassy in winning concession which involves
                    about $8,000,000. Announcement must not be made in United States but will soon
                    be made from Madrid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
